                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311020-216-off1155 t18311020-216-crimeloc1158"></join> about two o'clock in the afternoon, on the 20th of October, and lost a handkerchief; there was a crowd, as His Majesty was going to prorogue Parliament; a witness secured the prisoner, and I saw my handkerchief in his hand.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18311020-216-person1445">
                  JOHN 
                  SHEPHARD
               <interp inst="t18311020-216-person1445" type="surname" value="SHEPHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311020-216-person1445" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311020-216-person1445" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Police-constable. About two o'clock in the afternoon of the 20th of October I was in St. James'-park; I saw the prisoner and another, and watched them; the prosecutor and two other gentlemen stood seeing the carriage pass - I saw the prisoner go behind the prosecutor, and draw this handkerchief from his pocket; I seized his hand, and held it till the prosecutor saw it.</p>
